[The newly confirmed case of WPV1-associated polio in Afghanistan was in the media and covered in Poliomyelitis update (23): Afghanistan (OZ) 20190401.6398265. The good news in this update is no further reports of confirmed cases of cVDPV. That being said, the not-so-good news are the positive environmental samples of WPV1 in 3 of the 4 provinces of Pakistan (Punjab, Khyber Pakhtunkwha, and Sindh), with no positive samples reported from Balochistan. In addition, the positive environmental samples for cVDPV2 in Nigeria is also not-so-good news. The significance of the positive environmental samples is they are indicators of ongoing infections in the community, as the infected individuals are shedding the virus into the sewage.

