[The above MMWR article detailing the role and efforts of the surveillance activities towards global polio eradication is definitely worth reading. It gives a small glimpse at the enormity of the effort on a daily and annual basis to say the least. While many of the countries included in the findings met all surveillance standards at the national level, the events identified (occurrence of cVDPV-associated cases/outbreaks are shown to be due to having pocket of susceptibles (communities) at the sub-national level (e.g., districts) with significantly lower indicator performance than known to be necessary for interruption of transmission of the poliovirus and are ideal environments for the development of cVDPVs. - Mod.MPP]
